        <h1>About OAuch...</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-10 col-xl-6 offset-lg-1 offset-xl-2">
        <p>
            The OAuth 2.0 protocol is a popular and widely adopted authorization framework. Although it has been proven secure through comprehensive
            formal security analyses, new vulnerabilities continue to emerge in widely used OAuth implementations. OAuch aims to improve the overall
            security of the OAuth ecosystem by evaluating how well individual authorization servers adhere to the security specifications defined in
            the OAuth standards. It also provides detailed, targeted feedback to operators to help enhance the compliance and security of their services.
            OAuch tests and analyzes authorization servers based on the guidelines of the OAuth 2.0 standards and established security best practices.
        </p>
        <p>
            OAuch is developed by <a href="https://distrinet.cs.kuleuven.be/" target="_blank">the Distrinet Research Group</a> as part of a research initiative
            focused on API security. It is available for free and the source code can be accessed
            <a href="https://github.com/DistriNet/OAuch" target="_blank">on GitHub</a>. For inquiries, contact the OAuch team at <a href="mailto:info@oauch.io">info@oauch.io</a>.
        </p>
    </div>
